You're missing the `BindingContext`. The `{Binding}` markup works only when the page's `BindingContext` is set to your ViewModel instance.

**Fix — set it in code-behind:**

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
    }
}
```

**Or in XAML:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:local="clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels"
             ...>
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <local:MyViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>
    ...
</ContentPage>
```

Also make sure your ViewModel implements `INotifyPropertyChanged` (or inherits `ObservableObject` from the MVVM Toolkit) so the UI updates when property values change.
